column5: Hello  Well after posting yesterday on who would like to fish tomorrow,  JEN from Team 5      (which by the way is going to win the tourny)  pm'ed me and we went to Keswick for some fishing...  First I would like to say thank you Jen for fishing with me today...I had a amazing time.  For the people who dont know her,  she is like the perfect women..    she is into everything, she shoots, hunts, fish and by fishing I mean she will do any thing, (even take off my catfish EHEEH) and to boot a devoted mom of 3..  All I can say is WOW>  Anyway we went to Keswick today to do some  crappie fishing,   we meet at Yorkdale and proceeded to our fishing spot... Fishing today was amazing. right away Jen and I were catching fish,  a Crappie here and then 10 Bluegill in a row some sunfish and then more bluegills....  All and all between us we probally caught close to 70-80 fish...  On the way home we reliazed that we caught a huge array of different fish...  8  differnt species of fish.  IncludingCrappie, Bluegills, Sunfish, Perch, Largemouth Bass, Smallmouth Bass, Catfish, and Jen caught a good size Golden Shiner  Before anyone says anything the OOS fish were all released quickly and were not targeted  We have pics to follow and I would liket o thank Jen again, and lets plan something soon, mabye with your boys and I know my daughter would love to come as well..  Here is one pic, bewfore my camera died...   Dave
nice, sounds like u two had a good day
can't wait to see the pics ..glad you 2 had a good day ..
Steve I was gonna say the same thing, took the words from outta my mouth! LOL  Gerritt.

Yet again I have had the opportunity to meet another wonderful member of the OFC community.  Thank you so much Dave, for hanging out with me today.  Had a great day! Not to mention all the tips I picked up along the way.  Now lets just see if I can get my kids out there and onto the kind of fishing we had today.  Again, Thanks
Couple more pics from today!
Looks like it was a great day, great pics too.  Maureen
very nice and to think I use to camp right there some 40 years ago.........aaaahhhhh
Looks like a great day to be out fishing. Thanks for the report.

Great report!  Good to see more OFNers getting together and having a great time out there.  Sounded like a great day with LOTS and LOTS of fish!  My 5 year old loves places like that....we can never get her to leave....LOL
Wow,  It sounds like panfish paradise.  Perhaps I should drive out to Keswick instead of trying my luck at Grenadier Pond.

Its really alot of fun when you hook many different species keep up the good work guys. Nice pics and walking_angler dont put to much faith in grenadier pond i have almost made my breaking point never have any luck there was their saturday morning and not even a nibble.
Great!  Always nice to read about fellow OFNers getting together , having a great day and catching fish!  Congrats on the tourney entries Jen!!  bly
Great shots! congrats on the great day fishing...

Always glad to read reports from OFNers who hook up for fishing trips. Sounds like a fun day of panfishing too.  love_fishin and walking_angler, don't give up on Grenadier Pond. I used to live around High Park and saw a fair # of fish caught there, but in the summer. It's still much too cold, I don't think it gets good until late May or June.  Mike
You guys missed out on the world's greatest sport fish, rock bass!
Great report you two.  Nice to see for sure.  I don't think that red nailpolish suits you tho Dave.  Joey
I was thinking the same thing Joey....lol  Nice to see you both had a good time.  Nauti.
Looks like a super day  Any day you can catch a fish, is a great day!!!!!!

What's wrong with Grenadier Pond? I grew up in the High Park area and spend many days cycling down to and fishing Grenadier Pond. Over the years we've caught Large & Smallmouth Bass, Northern Pike, Black Crappies, Yellow Perch, Bluegills, Pumpkinseeds, Brown Bullheads, Common Carp and even Glizzard Shad. Great fishing area especially in the middle of Toronto! I still like to get down there and walk around. Cheers, Dave
right on looks like you gus had alot of fun!  cheers!
